Description:
  Generate a skeleton for a mirrOS_api data source

Example:
  rails generate mirros_source NAME
  rails generate mirros_source NAME field_1:type field_2:type

  Available types:
    string
    integer
    float

This will create:
  sources/NAME
  sources/NAME/Gemfile
  sources/NAME/MIT-LICENSE
  sources/NAME/README.md
  sources/NAME/Rakefile
  sources/NAME/.gitignore
  sources/NAME/app/assets/icons/NAME.svg
  sources/NAME/app/assets/templates/settings.vue
  sources/NAME/app/controllers/NAME/application_controller.rb
  sources/NAME/app/jobs/NAME/application_job.rb
  sources/NAME/app/mailers/NAME/application_mailer.rb
  sources/NAME/app/models/NAME/application_record.rb
  sources/NAME/app/models/NAME/NAME_data.rb
  sources/NAME/bin/rails
  sources/NAME/NAME.gemspec
  sources/NAME/config/routes.rb
  sources/NAME/lib/NAME.rb
  sources/NAME/lib/NAME/engine.rb
  sources/NAME/lib/NAME/fetcher.rb
  sources/NAME/lib/NAME/version.rb
  sources/NAME/lib/tasks/NAME_tasks.rake
  sources/NAME/test/NAME_test.rb
  sources/NAME/test/integration/navigation_test.rb
  sources/NAME/test/test_helper.rb
